name: r-ics
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '1.3-1' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-ics
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/ICS_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/ICS/ICS_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 9106f6bf89c57af44e89ea174150376e6dfba861cd78fcd0f26f45f637e46c74

build:
  noarch: generic
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1002
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-mvtnorm
    - r-survey
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-mvtnorm
    - r-survey

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('ICS')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('ICS')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=ICS
  license: GPL-2.0-or-later
  summary: 'Implementation of Tyler, Critchley, Duembgen and Oja''s (JRSS B, 2009, <doi:10.1111/j.1467-9868.2009.00706.x>)
    and Oja, Sirkia and Eriksson''s (AJS, 2006, <http://www.ajs.or.at/index.php/ajs/article/view/vol35,%20no2%263%20-%207>)
    method of two different scatter matrices to obtain an invariant coordinate system
    or independent components, depending on the underlying assumptions. '
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file: '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - MathiasHaudgaard
    - FrodePedersen
    - ArneKr
